item.description:
arXiv:2303.15856v2 Announce Type: replace 
Abstract: Let $A(n)$ denote the $(1,n)\text{-th}$ Fourier coefficient of a $SL(3, \mathbb{Z})$ Hecke eigenform or the ternary divisor function $d_3(n)$. Let $Q(x,y)$ be a symmetric positive definite quadratic form. This article establishes an asymptotic formula with a power-saving error term for the following sum \begin{equation*}
  \sum_{1 \leqslant m \leqslant X} \sum_{1 \leqslant n\leqslant Y} A(Q(m,n)), \end{equation*} where $X>1$ and $Y\leqslant X$.
